                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d91">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">867n.6363/7: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Jerusalem</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Southard</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Jerusalem</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-10-20T14:00:00+02:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 20, 1921—2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 3:52 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Referring to Department’s instruction of August 29<note n="42" xml:id="d91fn42"
                        >Not printed.</note> matter of Standard Oil Co. Permission for prospecting
                    has been referred from London to Jerusalem for recommendation. This Government
                    has permitted meetings informally to discuss it and assure me that it is being
                    now returned to London with favorable recommendation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Southard</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
